Hertzsprungâ€“Russell diagram: shows relationship between absolute magnitude and spectral class of stars
Absolute magniture: apparent magnitude at distance of 10 parsecs
Apparent magniture: brightness of star observed from Earth, reverse logarithmic

#Apparent magnitudes
Sun: -26
Moon: -12
Jupiter: -3/-1.7
Sirius: -1.4
Arcturus: 0
Vega: 0
Betelgeuse: 0.5
Polaris: 2

#Spectral class: temperature of shell
Class O: blue, hottest, rarest
Class B: blue (Rigel)
Class A: white (Sirius, Deneb, Vega)
Class F: white
Class G: yellow (Sun)
Class K: orange (Arcturus)
Class M: red, most common (Betelgeuse)
Class L: brown
Class T: brown

#Luminosity class
0: hypergiant
I: supergiant (Betelgeuse, Rigel, Deneb)
II: bright giant
III: giant (Arcturus)
IV: subgiant
V: dwarf (Sun, Sirius, Vega)
VI: subdwarf
VII: white dwarf
